A Xinjiang court has sentenced three men to death for attempting to hijack an aircraft in June. A fourth man was sentenced to life in prison.

The hijack attempt was made just 10 minutes after the Urumqi-bound plane took off from Hotian in southern Xinjiang, on June 29.

The hijackers, wielding aluminum pipes, tried to storm the cockpit but were beaten back by both crew and passengers. At least 10 people, including four crew members, were injured in the attack....
